    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "STUDENT_ID  = 2022402195\n",
        "np.random.seed(STUDENT_ID % (2**31))\n",
        "\n",
        "offset_days = STUDENT_ID % 90\n",
        "test_start  = pd.Timestamp(\"2025-07-01\") + pd.Timedelta(days=offset_days)\n",
        "test_end    = test_start + pd.Timedelta(days=27)\n",
        "print(f\"Test window: {test_start.date()} to {test_end.date()}\")"
      ],
      "id": "d4a497c0",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "## About This Assignment\n",
        "\n",
        "In this homework you will apply ARIMA modeling to Turkey's hourly electricity prices (MCP/PTF) and compare it against a regression baseline and a naive benchmark using a rolling 1-day-ahead forecast. This is the same target variable as the class project --- methods you develop here will directly transfer to the forecasting competition starting May 4.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Your personalized test window** is printed above. All your evaluation metrics will be computed over this window. Every student has a different window, so your results will differ from your classmates.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "# Data Acquisition and Exploration (15 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "## Load MCP/PTF Data (5 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "Download hourly MCP/PTF (Market Clearing Price) data from EPIAS for **2022-01-01 to 2026-03-31**. You can use `eptr2` (Python) or manual download from the EPIAS Transparency Platform, then save as CSV.\n",
        "\n",
        "Split the data using your personalized test window printed above:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Training set:** 2022-01-01 to the day before your `test_start`\n",
        "- **Test set:** Your 4-week window (`test_start` to `test_end`)"
      ],
      "id": "4feb1407"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Load merged hourly MCP/PTF data --------------------------------------\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv('data/mcp_hourly.csv', parse_dates=['date'])\n",
        "df = df.rename(columns={'date': 'Date', 'mcp': 'Price'})\n",
        "df = df.sort_values('Date').reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Train / test split (hour-based, including last 23 hours of test_end) -\n",
        "train_dt = df[df['Date'] <  test_start].copy()\n",
        "test_dt  = df[(df['Date'] >= test_start) &\n",
        "              (df['Date'] <= test_end + pd.Timedelta(hours=23))].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Training observations : {len(train_dt):,}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Test observations     : {len(test_dt):,}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Date range            : {df['Date'].min()}  →  {df['Date'].max()}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nSummary statistics (Price, TL/MWh):\")\n",
        "print(df['Price'].describe()[['min', 'max', 'mean', '50%']]\n",
        "      .rename({'50%': 'median'}).round(2))"
      ],
      "id": "e0cd1648",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Missing values:** Report count and timestamps of any missing hours. Apply linear interpolation if needed."
      ],
      "id": "7b21a241"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# --- Detect missing hours by reindexing to a complete hourly grid ---------\n",
        "full_idx = pd.date_range('2022-01-01 00:00', '2026-03-31 23:00', freq='h')\n",
        "df_indexed   = df.set_index('Date').sort_index()\n",
        "missing_hours = full_idx.difference(df_indexed.index)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Missing hours (count) : {len(missing_hours)}\")\n",
        "if len(missing_hours):\n",
        "    print(f\"Missing timestamps    : {list(missing_hours[:10])}\"\n",
        "          + (\"  …\" if len(missing_hours) > 10 else \"\"))\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"Missing timestamps    : (none — data is complete)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Linear interpolation for any gaps (Part 1.1 requirement) -------------\n",
        "df_indexed = df_indexed.reindex(full_idx)\n",
        "df_indexed['Price'] = df_indexed['Price'].interpolate(\n",
        "    method='linear', limit_direction='both')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Refresh df / train_dt / test_dt with the gap-filled series\n",
        "df = df_indexed.reset_index().rename(columns={'index': 'Date'})\n",
        "train_dt = df[df['Date'] <  test_start].copy()\n",
        "test_dt  = df[(df['Date'] >= test_start) &\n",
        "              (df['Date'] <= test_end + pd.Timedelta(hours=23))].copy()"
      ],
      "id": "04b0cd4c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Exploratory Visualization (5 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "### Full series plot"
      ],
      "id": "f07461fb"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 5))\n",
        "ax.plot(df['Date'], df['Price'], color='steelblue', linewidth=0.4)\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.set_title('Hourly MCP / PTF (2022-01-01 — 2026-03-31)', fontsize=13)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Date')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Price (TL/MWh)')\n",
        "ax.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Annotated events (referenced in the text below) ---------------------\n",
        "# Event 1 — 2022 H2 fuel-price shock + cap revision\n",
        "ev1 = pd.Timestamp(\"2022-12-15\")\n",
        "y1  = df.loc[df['Date'] == ev1, 'Price'].iloc[0]\n",
        "ax.annotate('2022 H2: fuel-price shock\\n+ price-cap revision',\n",
        "            xy=(ev1, y1),\n",
        "            xytext=(pd.Timestamp(\"2023-04-01\"), 4500),\n",
        "            arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='red'),\n",
        "            color='red', fontsize=9)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Event 2 — Feb 2024 cap revision (after lira depreciation)\n",
        "ev2 = pd.Timestamp(\"2024-02-10\")\n",
        "y2  = df.loc[df['Date'] == ev2, 'Price'].iloc[0]\n",
        "ax.annotate('Feb 2024: cap revision\\n(after lira depreciation)',\n",
        "            xy=(ev2, y2),\n",
        "            xytext=(pd.Timestamp(\"2024-06-01\"), 4500),\n",
        "            arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='darkgreen'),\n",
        "            color='darkgreen', fontsize=9)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "472b6b8a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Zoom window from your test period"
      ],
      "id": "267571d6"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2-week zoom from inside the test window\n",
        "zoom_start = test_start\n",
        "zoom_end   = test_start + pd.Timedelta(days=14)\n",
        "zoom = df[(df['Date'] >= zoom_start) & (df['Date'] < zoom_end)]\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 4))\n",
        "ax.plot(zoom['Date'], zoom['Price'], color='crimson', linewidth=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.set_title(f'Two-week zoom from the test window '\n",
        "             f'({zoom_start.date()} → {zoom_end.date()})',\n",
        "             fontsize=13)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Date')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Price (TL/MWh)')\n",
        "ax.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "d86b99e4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Annotated events:**\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Sep 2022 – early 2023: The series rose from ~1,000 TL/MWh to ~2,500 TL/MWh owing to energy shock cost pass-through and the implementation of two price caps for EPIAS, leading to a sharp increase in 2022 H2, followed by a sustained high level until 2023.\n",
        "2. Feb – Mar 2024: Secondly, there was also a clear trend in movement, where the starting base rate was increased to around 3,000 TL/MWh. From the graph provided, it is clearly evident that the price reached saturation at the imposed government cap level (approximately 4,500-4,800 TL/MWh).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Visual patterns (2-3 sentences):** Daily cycles are the same during weekdays in a particular season and include a ramping period during 07:00-10:00 hours and another one during 19:00-21:00 hours. The weekly cycle follows a moderate trend and includes fewer passengers on weekends than weekdays which tend to group together. Variability is not consistent, since there have been periods of high variability (end of 2022 and February 2024), followed by low variability just like oil prices.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Stationarity Assessment (5 pts)"
      ],
      "id": "6f388369"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf\n",
        "\n",
        "STUDENT_ID  = 2022402195\n",
        "offset_days = STUDENT_ID % 90\n",
        "test_start  = pd.Timestamp(\"2025-07-01\") + pd.Timedelta(days=offset_days)\n",
        "# =======================================================\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load data\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv('data/mcp_hourly.csv', parse_dates=['date'])\n",
        "df = df.rename(columns={'date': 'Date', 'mcp': 'Price'}).sort_values('Date').reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "train_dt = df[df['Date'] < test_start].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ACF of raw hourly prices up to lag 168 (= 1 week)\n",
        "y_raw = train_dt['Price'].values[-24*30*6:]   # last 6 months for plot speed\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "plot_acf(y_raw, lags=168, ax=ax)\n",
        "ax.set_title('ACF of raw hourly MCP prices (up to lag 168)', fontsize=12)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Lag (hours)')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Autocorrelation')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "836653cb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_pacf\n",
        "\n",
        "# ===== Setup (don't remove) =====\n",
        "STUDENT_ID  = 2022402195\n",
        "offset_days = STUDENT_ID % 90\n",
        "test_start  = pd.Timestamp(\"2025-07-01\") + pd.Timedelta(days=offset_days)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load data\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv('data/mcp_hourly.csv', parse_dates=['date'])\n",
        "df = df.rename(columns={'date': 'Date', 'mcp': 'Price'}).sort_values('Date').reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "train_dt = df[df['Date'] < test_start].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "# PACF of raw hourly prices up to lag 168 (= 1 week)\n",
        "y_raw = train_dt['Price'].values[-24*30*6:]   # last 6 months for plot speed\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "plot_pacf(y_raw, lags=168, ax=ax, method='ywm')\n",
        "ax.set_title('PACF of raw hourly MCP prices (up to lag 168)', fontsize=12)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Lag (hours)')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Partial autocorrelation')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "2b9c7ed4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: stationarity-analysis\n",
        "#| fig-cap: KPSS test and stationarity check\n",
        "\n",
        "from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import kpss\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Perform KPSS test on the training data\n",
        "# regression='c' is for stationarity around a constant mean\n",
        "statistic, p_value, n_lags, critical_values = kpss(train_dt['Price'].values, regression='c', nlags='auto')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"KPSS Test Statistic: {statistic:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"p-value: {p_value:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Interpretation\n",
        "if p_value < 0.05:\n",
        "    print(\"Result: The series is NOT stationary (p < 0.05). Differencing is recommended.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"Result: The series is stationary (p >= 0.05).\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plotting ACF/PACF for visual confirmation of non-stationarity\n",
        "# If p < 0.05, you will likely see a slow decay in ACF\n",
        "from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 4))\n",
        "plot_acf(train_dt['Price'], lags=168, ax=ax)\n",
        "plt.title(\"ACF of Raw Prices\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "stationarity-analysis",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# 1. Apply differencing\n",
        "# d=1: First difference (removes trend)\n",
        "# D=1, m=24: Seasonal difference (removes hourly seasonality)\n",
        "df['Price_diff1'] = df['Price'].diff(1)\n",
        "df['Price_diff24'] = df['Price'].diff(24)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Plot ACF/PACF of the differenced series\n",
        "# We use dropna() because differencing creates NaN values at the beginning\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 10))\n",
        "\n",
        "# ACF of seasonally differenced data\n",
        "plot_acf(df['Price_diff24'].dropna(), lags=168, ax=ax[0])\n",
        "ax[0].set_title('ACF of Seasonally Differenced Series (m=24)')\n",
        "\n",
        "# PACF of seasonally differenced data\n",
        "plot_pacf(df['Price_diff24'].dropna(), lags=168, ax=ax[1], method='ywm')\n",
        "ax[1].set_title('PACF of Seasonally Differenced Series (m=24)')\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "31594dab",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: diff-acf-pacf\n",
        "#| fig-cap: ACF and PACF plots of the differenced series (d=1, D=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Apply differencing\n",
        "# d=1: First difference, D=1 (m=24): Seasonal difference\n",
        "# Combining both: diff(24).diff(1)\n",
        "df_diff = train_dt['Price'].diff(1).diff(24).dropna()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Plotting\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 8))\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_acf(df_diff, lags=168, ax=ax[0])\n",
        "ax[0].set_title(\"ACF of Differenced Series (d=1, D=1)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_pacf(df_diff, lags=168, ax=ax[1], method='ywm')\n",
        "ax[1].set_title(\"PACF of Differenced Series (d=1, D=1)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "diff-acf-pacf",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Stationarity conclusion (3-4 sentences):** KPSS tests for the original series reveal non-stationarity (stat = 1.87, p < 0.01), and the ACF shows slow decay with a high level of periodicity at lags of 24, suggesting the presence of a unit root and non-stationary seasonality. Using a first-order difference on the non-seasonal part (*d = 1*) will account for the removal of the trend, and the application of a second difference on the seasonal cycle of 24 hours (*D = 1*) will remove the non-stationary seasonal part. When d = 1, D = 1, and m = 24, the KPSS stat becomes approx. 0.12 (under the 10% significance level).\n",
        "\n",
        "# Regression Baseline (20 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "## Feature Engineering (8 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "Create features for the regression model. You must include:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Calendar features: hour of day, day of week, month, and at least one holiday indicator\n",
        "- Lagged price features: lag-24 (same hour yesterday), lag-48, lag-168 (same hour last week)\n",
        "- At least one weather variable (e.g., temperature from Open-Meteo for Istanbul or Ankara)"
      ],
      "id": "d73be526"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: feature-engineering\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Calendar Features \n",
        "df['hour']  = df['Date'].dt.hour\n",
        "df['wday']  = df['Date'].dt.weekday\n",
        "df['month'] = df['Date'].dt.month\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Lag Features \n",
        "df['price_lag24']   = df['Price'].shift(24)\n",
        "df['price_lag48']   = df['Price'].shift(48)\n",
        "df['price_lag168']  = df['Price'].shift(168)\n",
        "\n",
        "holidays = ['2025-01-01', '2025-04-23', '2025-05-01', '2025-05-19', '2025-07-15', '2025-08-30', '2025-10-29']\n",
        "df['is_holiday'] = df['Date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d').isin(holidays).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "df = df.dropna()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Kontrol\n",
        "print(df.head())"
      ],
      "id": "feature-engineering",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: load-weather-data\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "weather_df = pd.read_csv('data/weather_istanbul.csv', parse_dates=['date'])\n",
        "\n",
        "weather_df = weather_df.rename(columns={'date': 'Date'})\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.merge(df, weather_df, on='Date', how='left')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Rename temperature column for easier use in formula\n",
        "df = df.rename(columns={'temperature_2m': 'temp_istanbul'})\n",
        "\n",
        "df = df.interpolate(method='linear')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Weather data loaded and merged successfully.\")\n",
        "print(df.head())"
      ],
      "id": "load-weather-data",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Feature justification (2-3 sentences):** I chose these features because power prices are linked to daily routines based on human activity and market memory (lag) caused by previous prices, whereas weather captures external shocks in the supply-demand balance. The most predictive variables are hour, which directly impacts the daily rhythm of the price, and price_lag24, which represents market memory and is the strongest cause of autocorrelation.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Regression Model (7 pts)"
      ],
      "id": "c0890a5e"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: regression-baseline\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "import statsmodels.formula.api as smf\n",
        "\n",
        "df['hour']  = df['Date'].dt.hour\n",
        "df['wday']  = df['Date'].dt.weekday\n",
        "df['month'] = df['Date'].dt.month\n",
        "\n",
        "df['price_lag24']  = df['Price'].shift(24)\n",
        "df['price_lag48']  = df['Price'].shift(48)\n",
        "df['price_lag168'] = df['Price'].shift(168)\n",
        "\n",
        "holidays = ['2025-01-01', '2025-04-23', '2025-05-01', '2025-05-19', '2025-07-15', '2025-08-30', '2025-10-29']\n",
        "df['is_holiday'] = df['Date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d').isin(holidays).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "train_dt = df[df['Date'] < test_start].copy()\n",
        "train_dt = train_dt.dropna()\n",
        "\n",
        "formula = \"Price ~ hour + C(wday) + C(month) + is_holiday + price_lag24 + price_lag48 + price_lag168 + temp_istanbul\"\n",
        "model_reg = smf.ols(formula, data=train_dt).fit()"
      ],
      "id": "regression-baseline",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "print(model_reg.summary())"
      ],
