    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Residual assessment (2-3 sentences):** According to Ljung-Box test results, residuals from the regression are not white noise for lags 24, 48, and 168 (p<0.05). In particular, p-value for lag 168 (p=0.000) proves the absence of fit to the weekly periodicity, indicating that there is no account of 7-day periodicity in the electricity price in the baseline regression model. Furthermore, p-value for lag 24 (p=0.048) proves that although the model takes into account daily periodicity to some degree, it is still insufficient.\n",
        "\n",
        "# ARIMA Modeling (30 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "## Box-Jenkins on Differenced Prices (10 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "Using the differencing order you determined in Part 1.3, examine the ACF/PACF to propose candidate ARIMA orders.\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-tip}\n",
        "## Computation Note\n",
        "ARIMA fitting on long hourly series can be slow. For initial exploration, consider using a recent subset of training data (e.g., last 6 months). Use `stepwise=TRUE, approximation=TRUE` in `auto.arima()` for faster fitting.\n",
        ":::"
      ],
      "id": "85227be7"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: arima-identification\n",
        "#| fig-cap: ACF and PACF for ARIMA parameter identification\n",
        "\n",
        "from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "diff_series = train_dt['Price'].diff(1).diff(24).dropna()\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 10))\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_acf(diff_series, lags=168, ax=ax[0])\n",
        "ax[0].set_title(\"ACF of Differenced Series (Identification for q, Q)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_pacf(diff_series, lags=168, ax=ax[1], method='ywm')\n",
        "ax[1].set_title(\"PACF of Differenced Series (Identification for p, P)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "arima-identification",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
