        "**Model comparison table:**\n",
        "Model,    \"Order (p,d,q)\",           AIC,        In-sample RMSE\n",
        "ARIMA 1,  \"(1, 1, 1)\",               \"463,994\",  392.15\n",
        "ARIMA 2,  \"(1, 1, 1)(1, 1, 1, 24)\",  \"452,026\",  314.84\n",
        "ARIMA 3,  \"(0, 1, 1)(0, 1, 1, 24)\",  \"452,026\",  327.52\n",
        "\n",
        "**Model selection (2-3 sentences):** The ACF and PACF plots helped us determine that the appropriate time series structure was SARIMA(1,1,1)(1,1,1,24). As the prices were not stationary, it required us to difference them once, that is $d=1$. Since there were significant spikes at lag 1 in the ACF and PACF plots, it indicated the presence of AR(1) and MA(1). Finally, due to the spikes at lags 24, 48, and 72, we could say that there was a strong daily seasonality, which necessitated the inclusion of seasonal parameters as (1,1,1,24).\n",
        "\n",
        "## Seasonal ARIMA (10 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "Extend to SARIMA(p,d,q)(P,D,Q)₂₄ with m=24 (hourly seasonality).\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-tip}\n",
        "## Computation Note\n",
        "Seasonal ARIMA with m=24 can be very slow on long series. Use `stepwise=TRUE, approximation=TRUE` and consider limiting to the most recent training data. Fitting may take several minutes.\n",
        ":::"
      ],
      "id": "c4cc1587"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: modeling-pipeline\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
        "import warnings\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ignore convergence warnings for a cleaner report\n",
        "warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\n",
        "\n",
        "train_subset = train_dt['Price'].tail(24 * 180)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 1. Manual SARIMA ---\n",
        "print(\"Fitting Manual SARIMA...\")\n",
        "model_sarima = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(train_subset, \n",
        "                       order=(1, 1, 1), \n",
        "                       seasonal_order=(1, 1, 1, 24),\n",
        "                       enforce_stationarity=False,\n",
        "                       enforce_invertibility=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "results_sarima = model_sarima.fit(disp=False, maxiter=50)\n",
        "print(results_sarima.summary())\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 2. Auto-ARIMA Fallback ---\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    import pmdarima as pm\n",
        "    print(\"\\nFitting Auto-ARIMA...\")\n",
        "    sarima_model = pm.auto_arima(train_subset,\n",
        "                                 seasonal=True,\n",
        "                                 m=24,\n",
        "                                 stepwise=True,\n",
        "                                 approximation=True,\n",
        "                                 trace=True)\n",
        "    print(sarima_model.summary()"
      ],
      "id": "modeling-pipeline",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: final-forecasting\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Use the fitted model to forecast the length of test_dt\n",
        "forecast = results_sarima.forecast(steps=len(test_dt))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Define WMAPE\n",
        "def calculate_wmape(y_true, y_pred):\n",
        "    return (np.sum(np.abs(y_true - y_pred)) / np.sum(np.abs(y_true))) * 100\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate metrics\n",
        "rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(test_dt['Price'], forecast))\n",
        "wmape = calculate_wmape(test_dt['Price'], forecast)\n",
        "mae = mean_absolute_error(test_dt['Price'], forecast)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Final Model Performance:\")\n",
        "print(f\"RMSE: {rmse:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"WMAPE: {wmape:.2f}%\")\n",
        "print(f\"MAE: {mae:.4f}\")"
      ],
      "id": "final-forecasting",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
